WEBVTT

00:04.433 --> 00:09.433
(breeze and birds chirping)

00:13.400 --> 00:15.833
(snoring)

00:15.833 --> 00:19.800
(alarm clock)

00:19.800 --> 00:31.467
(radio spokesman)

00:35.433 --> 00:39.567
(Waiting For A Train
by Jimmie Rodgers)

00:39.567 --> 00:43.833
* All around the water tank

00:43.833 --> 00:48.433
* Waiting for a train

00:48.433 --> 00:52.567
* A thousand miles
away from home,

00:52.567 --> 00:57.367
* Sleeping in the rain

00:57.367 --> 01:01.300
* I walked up to a brakeman

01:01.300 --> 01:05.233
* To give him a line of talk

01:05.233 --> 01:09.567
* He said "If you got money"

01:09.567 --> 01:14.100
* I'll see that you don't walk
You won't have to walk

01:14.100 --> 01:18.300
* I haven't got a nickel

01:18.300 --> 01:22.867
* Not a penny can I show

01:22.867 --> 01:27.767
* "Get off, get off,
you railroad bum"

01:27.767 --> 02:06.900
* And slammed the boxcar door

02:11.367 --> 02:16.900
(cat yelping)

02:21.400 --> 02:23.600
(screaming)

02:25.067 --> 03:49.300
(soft sad harmonica music)

03:53.500 --> 03:56.700
Roger, I'll never forget you.

03:59.267 --> 04:01.833
You were always there for me.

04:01.833 --> 04:04.600
A true friend to the end.

04:06.733 --> 04:10.500
No words could sum up
the heartbreak I feel.

04:13.933 --> 04:18.533
I remember when I went to
the pet shop to get you.

04:21.067 --> 04:24.333
I liked another
kitten in the box.

04:26.400 --> 04:29.433
But you were crying

04:31.200 --> 04:33.933
and you wanted me.

04:33.933 --> 04:37.067
You were a great
companion all these years.

04:39.300 --> 04:42.267
I love you, Roger.

04:43.900 --> 04:48.167
I'm sorry I ran over you.

04:48.167 --> 04:54.067
(ice cream truck music)

04:58.400 --> 05:00.900
(tires screeching)

05:00.900 --> 05:02.400
You okay, Dylan?

05:02.400 --> 05:03.933
I'm okay, Warren.

05:03.933 --> 05:05.633
I'm good.

05:08.333 --> 05:13.100
(train horn)

05:15.767 --> 05:16.633
What flavor?

05:16.633 --> 05:18.567
Mmm, chocolate.

05:20.100 --> 05:21.467
What's that supposed to mean?

05:21.467 --> 05:23.333
You know what it means.

05:24.700 --> 05:29.200
Can I get one single
serve of chocolate please?

05:29.200 --> 05:31.367
Cup or cone?

05:31.367 --> 05:33.367
Cone, thanks.

05:34.500 --> 05:39.500
(giggling)

05:41.933 --> 05:42.833
Thanks.

05:42.833 --> 05:43.900
What do I owe you, mate?

05:43.900 --> 05:46.367
That's $2.90.

05:46.367 --> 05:47.933
There you go.

05:47.933 --> 05:49.233
Is it good?

05:49.233 --> 05:50.200
Mhmm.

05:50.200 --> 05:51.867
No.

05:54.767 --> 05:56.100
Oh shit.

05:56.100 --> 05:59.333
Hey mate, you got
something on your tire.

06:00.833 --> 06:01.633
Where?

06:01.633 --> 06:04.333
Just here man.

06:08.800 --> 06:11.767
It's Roger.

06:11.767 --> 06:15.067
I'm sorry, what?

06:15.067 --> 06:16.900
My cat.

06:16.900 --> 06:20.100
I accidentally killed him.

06:20.100 --> 06:22.133
I'm really sorry.

06:22.133 --> 06:23.133
Are you okay?

06:23.133 --> 06:24.300
I'll get your change.

06:24.300 --> 06:24.933
Hey, come on, man.

06:24.933 --> 06:25.867
That's fine.

06:25.867 --> 06:27.700
Just keep the change, alright?

06:27.700 --> 06:30.100
I hope your day
gets better, buddy.

06:30.100 --> 06:30.733
Sorry.

06:30.733 --> 06:31.367
Thanks.

06:31.367 --> 06:32.433
(laughing)

06:32.433 --> 06:45.633
(soft sad music)

06:50.067 --> 06:50.800
Where you been?

06:50.800 --> 06:51.733
I been waiting for you!

06:51.733 --> 06:53.667
Fuck off!

06:53.667 --> 06:56.433
I told you to wait at the
fucking station for me.

06:56.433 --> 07:01.433
(couple screaming at each other)

07:04.400 --> 07:40.167
(soft dramatic music)

07:44.633 --> 07:49.633
(commercials)

07:51.733 --> 07:54.100
[Voiceover] Previously
on 'Round the Block.

07:54.100 --> 07:56.100
Where the hell do
you think you're going?

07:56.100 --> 07:57.267
I'm leaving.

07:57.267 --> 07:59.067
I've had it with this place.

07:59.067 --> 08:00.267
Damnit to hell, Slug.

08:00.267 --> 08:02.533
It's time to grow up.

08:02.533 --> 08:04.333
I'm not like you, Dad.

08:04.333 --> 08:06.600
I don't want to be like you.

08:06.600 --> 08:11.233
Just back off, old man.

08:15.467 --> 08:17.267
[Voiceover] Mornin' Dylan.

08:17.267 --> 08:19.300
[Voiceover] Morning.

08:19.300 --> 08:20.167
[Voiceover] Coffee.

08:20.167 --> 08:21.600
Yeah.

08:21.600 --> 08:23.933
Stace, have you seen Ralph?

08:23.933 --> 08:25.700
No. Why?

08:25.700 --> 08:30.433
Because since Slug left
town, no one has seen him.

08:30.433 --> 08:33.067
Really?

08:33.067 --> 08:34.799
Yeah.

08:34.799 --> 08:38.433
And he doesn't have
his heart medication.

08:38.433 --> 09:10.433
(theme music)

09:15.067 --> 09:16.967
Ralph.

09:16.967 --> 09:19.167
Ralph.

09:19.167 --> 09:21.333
Are you out there?

09:23.733 --> 09:25.567
Ralph.

09:25.567 --> 09:27.667
It's alright, Eileen.

09:27.667 --> 09:29.267
We'll find him.

09:29.267 --> 09:30.700
[Voiceover] I hope so.

09:30.700 --> 09:33.833
I don't know what I'd
do without my Ralph.

09:36.533 --> 09:39.167
I hope we find
him time, Stace.

09:39.167 --> 09:41.500
I'm really worried about him.

09:41.500 --> 09:43.967
I am too.

09:43.967 --> 09:46.100
But we'll find him.

09:47.167 --> 09:49.333
I love you, Stace.

09:49.333 --> 09:52.933
I love you, too.

09:52.933 --> 10:12.167
(heavy breathing)

10:16.633 --> 10:19.467
(alarm clock)

10:19.467 --> 10:23.367
(weather report on radio)

10:23.367 --> 10:36.867
(soft slow music)

10:41.233 --> 10:43.200
$5.90 in change.

10:43.200 --> 10:44.933
Thank you.

10:44.933 --> 10:47.067
You know what, actually.

10:49.567 --> 10:51.700
What kind have you got?

10:51.700 --> 10:53.300
I don't know?

10:57.267 --> 10:58.533
Hi Ruby.

10:58.533 --> 11:00.133
Morning, Warren.

11:00.133 --> 11:02.533
I'll pay for that, thanks.

11:04.700 --> 11:07.867
It's $56, thank you.

11:07.867 --> 11:10.133
Are you okay?

11:10.133 --> 11:11.733
Yeah.

11:11.733 --> 11:13.167
Yeah?

11:13.167 --> 11:15.433
What are those?

11:15.433 --> 11:18.100
Oh, we've just got a
couple of old cameras.

11:18.100 --> 11:20.500
A friends of mine wants
to get rid of them.

11:20.500 --> 11:21.500
Can I have a look?

11:21.500 --> 11:26.400
Yeah, sure.

11:30.867 --> 11:33.267
See you, Ruby.

11:33.267 --> 11:35.100
Well, wait.

11:35.100 --> 11:36.400
Before you go.

11:38.633 --> 11:42.200
I've got a few old
magazines, if you want them.

11:42.200 --> 11:45.567
I know you like reading
these, so I kept them.

11:45.567 --> 11:46.667
Thanks for doin' that.

11:46.667 --> 11:48.500
[Ruby] It's okay.

11:48.500 --> 11:49.200
See you, Ruby.

11:49.200 --> 11:51.233
Bye.

11:51.233 --> 12:16.100
(soft slow music)

12:20.100 --> 12:27.433
(suspenseful music
on television)

12:31.667 --> 12:34.767
Warren, is it ready yet?

12:34.767 --> 12:40.933
Warren?

12:45.300 --> 12:47.600
Go ahead, Dylan.

12:47.600 --> 12:49.467
Make my day.

12:49.467 --> 12:50.700
Thank you, Harry.

12:50.700 --> 12:53.067
You're Dirty Harry, Warren.

12:53.067 --> 12:54.667
What are you thinking?

12:54.667 --> 12:55.800
I don't know.

12:55.800 --> 12:58.300
It all looks really fattening.

12:58.300 --> 13:00.333
Oh, stuff it.

13:00.333 --> 13:01.467
Maybe some gelati?

13:01.467 --> 13:02.900
Gross.

13:02.900 --> 13:04.867
What are you on, bitch?

13:04.867 --> 13:06.267
Gelati's delicious.

13:06.267 --> 13:07.400
No, it's not.

13:07.400 --> 13:09.100
It's like ice cream
for old people.

13:09.100 --> 13:10.400
Shut up.

13:10.400 --> 13:11.667
Yeah, I told him,

13:11.667 --> 13:13.567
"You oughta get that
done by next Friday."

13:13.567 --> 13:15.667
Double scoop of
vanilla, please, mate.

13:18.100 --> 13:19.867
Well you tell that dickhead

13:19.867 --> 13:22.167
if it's not done by next
Friday, he's off the job.

13:22.167 --> 13:23.100
I don't care.

13:23.100 --> 13:24.467
I've fuckin' had it with him.

13:24.467 --> 13:26.367
Do you want nuts with that?

13:28.400 --> 13:30.667
You're fuckin' tellin' me.

13:30.667 --> 13:39.733
(train)

13:43.700 --> 13:46.533
Chuck us an ice
cream, ya cunt.

13:46.533 --> 13:48.567
What flavor do you want?

13:48.567 --> 13:49.933
What do you got?

13:49.933 --> 13:51.800
The menu's on the window.

13:51.800 --> 13:53.433
Well I don't want
to look at the menu.

13:53.433 --> 13:55.633
Just tell me what you got.

13:56.500 --> 13:57.633
Hurry up.

13:57.633 --> 13:59.800
I haven't got all day.

13:59.800 --> 14:03.633
Chocolate, coffee, vanilla.

14:03.633 --> 14:06.067
Fuckin' what else?

14:06.067 --> 14:11.067
Gelati, bubble
gum, strawberry.

14:11.400 --> 14:12.900
Strawberry.

14:12.900 --> 14:14.467
Give us one of those.

14:14.467 --> 14:15.500
Cup on cone?

14:15.500 --> 14:17.067
Well, what do you reckon?

14:17.067 --> 14:29.767
A cone, you cunt.

14:34.100 --> 14:36.567
You got any sprinkles?

14:36.567 --> 14:38.267
Yeah.

14:38.267 --> 14:47.067
Well, pop some
on there, would ya?

14:51.200 --> 15:01.900
It's fuckin' delicious, ya cunt.

15:06.367 --> 15:11.367
(soft sad music)

15:14.433 --> 15:19.433
(sad music and tape rewinding)

15:21.567 --> 15:25.533
(alarm clock)

15:25.533 --> 15:33.667
(radio weather report)

15:37.400 --> 15:41.600
You were the first thing
I'd see every morning.

15:42.567 --> 15:46.433
And when I'd come
home from work,

15:46.433 --> 15:51.400
you'd be in the
driveway waiting for me.

15:51.400 --> 15:54.400
You trusted me to
look after you,

15:54.400 --> 15:56.500
but I killed you.

15:56.500 --> 16:21.367
(soft sad music)

16:25.067 --> 16:27.967
[Voiceover] On tonight's
episode of 'Round the Block.

16:27.967 --> 16:30.233
Slug is back.

16:30.233 --> 16:33.233
And a storm is coming.

16:33.233 --> 16:35.133
What's going on?

16:35.133 --> 16:36.800
Slug's back.

16:36.800 --> 16:38.067
(crying)

16:38.067 --> 16:39.767
[Voiceover] There will
be a death on the block

16:39.767 --> 16:41.967
that will shock
you to your core.

16:43.533 --> 16:46.200
Weeknights at 7.

16:46.200 --> 17:08.067
(soft music)

17:12.500 --> 17:13.532
Hi, Ruby.

17:13.532 --> 17:14.833
Hey, Warren.

17:14.833 --> 17:17.133
Hey, I've been
thinking about it,

17:17.133 --> 17:19.166
and I'd like to buy one
of those cameras, please.

17:19.166 --> 17:21.166
Okay, cool.

17:21.166 --> 17:22.300
Any particular one?

17:22.300 --> 17:24.233
One that does video.

17:24.233 --> 17:25.733
Yep, no worries

17:27.233 --> 17:30.133
Hey, you'll never guess
what happened to me today.

17:30.133 --> 17:31.267
What?

17:31.267 --> 17:33.800
Katie George
came to my van and

17:33.800 --> 17:36.167
I spoke to her and
she had an ice cream.

17:36.167 --> 17:38.467
Do you have honeycomb?

17:39.533 --> 17:42.800
Just a scoop of that, thanks.

17:47.067 --> 17:49.167
I really love your show.

17:49.167 --> 17:50.900
I watch it every night.

17:50.900 --> 17:52.067
Really?

17:52.067 --> 17:54.133
Yeah, and I hope
you find Ralph.

17:54.133 --> 17:57.900
The show wouldn't be
the same without him.

17:57.900 --> 18:00.633
Who's Katie George?

18:00.633 --> 18:02.867
Katie George.

18:02.867 --> 18:05.767
I have no idea who that is.

18:06.967 --> 18:08.733
Do you watch 'Round the Block?

18:08.733 --> 18:10.800
What, the TV show?

18:10.800 --> 18:11.833
Yeah.

18:11.833 --> 18:13.500
No, I don't watch that crap.

18:13.500 --> 18:15.300
It's not crap.

18:15.300 --> 18:16.467
Sorry.

18:16.467 --> 18:18.067
It's my favorite show.

18:18.067 --> 18:20.300
And Katie George plays Stacey,

18:20.300 --> 18:22.467
and that's my
favorite character.

18:22.467 --> 18:23.667
Cool.

18:23.667 --> 18:25.133
Well don't you
think that's crazy?

18:25.133 --> 18:27.767
My favorite character coming
to my van to have ice cream?

18:27.767 --> 18:29.900
Yeah.

18:29.900 --> 18:33.333
Pretty cool, I guess.

18:37.700 --> 18:42.700
(heavy breathing)

18:46.433 --> 18:49.433
Hi.

18:53.433 --> 18:56.233
Hi, I'm Warren
Thompson and today

18:56.233 --> 18:58.233
the most amazing thing happened.

18:58.233 --> 19:01.667
The love of my life
came to my van.

19:01.667 --> 19:03.933
Everybody has
someone they worship.

19:03.933 --> 19:07.333
Whether it's an
actor or a singer,

19:07.333 --> 19:10.067
Everybody has someone they love

19:10.067 --> 19:14.267
like a soulmate and for
me it's Katie George.

19:14.267 --> 19:19.067
I bought this camera so
I could document when,

19:20.267 --> 19:23.400
well, if, she ever comes back.

19:23.400 --> 19:26.567
I thought we had
a real connection.

19:28.767 --> 19:31.633
I love you Katie George

19:31.633 --> 19:34.567
and I'm gonna make you mine.

19:36.433 --> 19:39.800
This is Warren, signing out.

19:41.667 --> 19:42.667
[Voiceover] I'll
never forgive Slug

19:42.667 --> 19:44.333
if anything happens to dad.

19:44.333 --> 19:46.467
[Voiceover] You
know what Slug's like.

19:46.467 --> 19:48.667
He's just a teenager.

19:48.667 --> 19:51.500
Yeah, but he's always
in and out of our lives,

19:51.500 --> 19:53.467
ruining everything.

19:53.467 --> 19:55.733
I've had it with him.

19:58.200 --> 19:59.467
Look.

19:59.467 --> 20:01.333
Dad.

20:01.333 --> 20:03.167
[Voiceover] Ralph!

20:04.200 --> 20:06.667
It's okay, doll.

20:08.433 --> 20:10.800
I'm sorry I left.

20:10.800 --> 20:14.567
After Slug went, I
just couldn't face you.

20:14.567 --> 20:17.467
[Voiceover] It's
okay, sweetheart.

20:17.467 --> 20:20.433
We can work through this.

20:20.433 --> 20:24.633
We are here for you.

20:29.000 --> 20:31.300
Come here, son.

20:32.467 --> 20:35.633
I love you, dad.

20:35.633 --> 20:38.733
I love you too, son.

20:42.633 --> 20:45.167
Okay, so, it's the
day after Katie George

20:45.167 --> 20:46.767
came into my life.

20:46.767 --> 20:49.500
It's a beautiful day outside.

20:49.500 --> 20:51.067
Good day for ice cream.

20:51.067 --> 20:53.467
I hope she comes back.

20:53.467 --> 20:55.633
We've got so much to talk about.

20:55.633 --> 20:59.333
Last night's show was
a genuine cliffhanger.

20:59.333 --> 21:02.767
I want to tell her
how good she was.

21:02.767 --> 21:05.800
She probably gets
that all the time.

21:05.800 --> 21:10.800
You know, Katie's a lot
like Stacey in real life.

21:11.167 --> 21:12.700
They're both beautiful.

21:12.700 --> 21:14.933
They're both friendly.

21:14.933 --> 21:18.800
I'd really love to
talk to her again.

21:18.800 --> 21:22.333
I've got so many questions
I want to ask her.

21:22.333 --> 21:24.633
Like, what's her favorite food?

21:24.633 --> 21:26.533
Her favorite movies?

21:26.533 --> 21:28.933
Does she like Clint Eastwood?

21:30.333 --> 21:33.233
Does she have a boyfriend?

21:33.233 --> 21:36.700
Anyway, I better be off now.

21:38.167 --> 21:40.467
Fingers crossed.

21:43.600 --> 21:44.800
You want an ice
cream, sweetie?

21:44.800 --> 21:46.667
Yeah.

21:46.667 --> 21:48.867
What kind do you want?

21:48.867 --> 21:51.300
Um, strawberry.

21:51.300 --> 21:52.267
Okay.

21:52.267 --> 21:53.700
Um, hi.

21:53.700 --> 21:58.200
Can I get a one scoop cone
of strawberry, thanks?

21:58.200 --> 21:59.533
Cone?

22:02.900 --> 22:04.900
When are we meeting dad?

22:04.900 --> 22:07.933
We're gonna go and
see him now, sweetie.

22:12.400 --> 22:15.367
That's $2.90.

22:18.067 --> 22:18.933
Warren?

22:18.933 --> 22:20.367
Yeah?

22:20.367 --> 22:23.067
Warren Thompson?

22:24.133 --> 22:26.800
Amanda.

22:26.800 --> 22:28.733
Yeah.

22:28.733 --> 22:31.400
Long time, no see, eh?

22:31.400 --> 22:32.767
Yeah.

22:32.767 --> 22:34.767
[Amanda] So, how ya been?

22:34.767 --> 22:36.667
Not bad.

22:36.667 --> 22:38.500
Yourself?

22:38.500 --> 22:41.267
Busy.

22:41.267 --> 22:43.400
So, you got kids?

22:43.400 --> 22:45.433
No.

22:45.433 --> 22:47.233
Married?

22:47.233 --> 22:49.433
No.

22:50.467 --> 22:53.867
Just been busy working, eh?

22:53.867 --> 22:56.767
Pretty much.

22:56.767 --> 22:58.700
Who's that.

22:58.700 --> 23:00.433
This is Warren.

23:00.433 --> 23:03.567
Warren and I used
to be good friends.

23:03.567 --> 23:06.067
Was he your boyfriend?

23:06.067 --> 23:08.067
Sorry.

23:08.067 --> 23:10.233
It's okay.

23:12.800 --> 23:16.200
Well, we better get going.

23:17.700 --> 23:19.733
It was nice seeing you.

23:19.733 --> 23:21.933
Yeah, same.

23:21.933 --> 23:23.567
Stay safe.

23:23.567 --> 23:25.600
Yeah, you too.

23:25.600 --> 23:26.533
See ya.

23:26.533 --> 23:37.200
Bye.

23:41.800 --> 23:43.133
Hey.

23:44.333 --> 23:46.800
Sorry, I didn't see ya there.

23:46.800 --> 23:48.500
How can I help you?

23:48.500 --> 23:50.400
Single scoop of vanilla.

23:50.400 --> 23:55.900
Okay.

24:00.400 --> 24:02.567
That's $2.90.

24:02.567 --> 24:11.067
With nuts.

24:15.600 --> 24:17.733
$3.70.

24:21.067 --> 24:39.667
Hey.

24:43.633 --> 24:47.600
I waited until 10
o'clock for her to come.

24:47.600 --> 24:49.633
But she didn't come.

24:49.633 --> 24:51.933
Maybe she was too busy.

24:51.933 --> 24:54.433
Or maybe she was in filming.

24:54.433 --> 24:57.467
She said that she
liked my ice cream.

24:57.467 --> 25:02.233
So, I think she'll come back.

25:06.200 --> 25:08.933
My van's getting
serviced tomorrow.

25:08.933 --> 25:11.233
So I might go and walk around

25:11.233 --> 25:14.133
and see if I can find
where they're filming.

25:15.433 --> 25:17.967
I could even take some
honeycomb ice cream

25:17.967 --> 25:20.067
on to set for her.

25:20.067 --> 25:23.267
I think she'd like that.

25:23.267 --> 25:27.067
Then maybe she might
start to see me

25:27.067 --> 25:30.267
like I see her.

25:34.733 --> 25:36.333
Hey, Warren.

25:36.333 --> 25:37.267
Warren.

25:37.267 --> 25:38.500
Hey, Dylan.

25:38.500 --> 25:40.067
[Dylan] Bye, Warren.

25:40.067 --> 25:42.133
See you later, mate.

25:42.133 --> 25:51.567
(Where Did You Sleep
